place.name: FIDDINGTON
place.gazetteerText: FIDDINGTON, a parish in Bridgewater district, Somerset; 3¼ miles SSW of Bridgewater bay, and 6 WNW of Bridgewater town and r. station. Post town, Cannington, under Bridgewater. Acres, 825. Real property, £923. Pop., 213. Houses, 53. The property is much subdivided. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Bath and Wells. Value, £200. Patron, the Rev. H. W. Rawlins. The church was repaired in 1859. There is an Independent chapel. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
